<p>Main paper can be found <a href="http://cmph.sourceforge.net/papers/esa09.pdf">here</a>.</p>

<ul>
  <li>CHD algorithm for generating perfect hash functions</li>
  <li>input is a set of â€˜nâ€™ keys, to be mapped to a space of â€˜mâ€™ numbers</li>
  <li>2-level hashing approach
    <ul>
      <li>first hash puts all input keys into â€˜râ€™ buckets</li>
      <li>then thereâ€™ll be multiple random hash functions</li>
      <li>out of which, one will be allocated to a given bucket</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>2 parameters controlling the behavior
    <ul>
      <li>lambda - number of keys per bucket (r = ceil(n / lambda))</li>
      <li>alpha - table load factor (m = ceil(n / alpha)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>in practice, heuristic hash functions proposed by Jenkins in
â€œAlgorithm Alley: Hash functionsâ€ Dr.Dobbs article is being used</li>
  <li>also supports k-perfect hash functions (but not my interest currently!)</li>
</ul>
